                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t18280529-153-victim890 t18280529-153-viclabel851"></join>. I lost a cap, two aprons, and a shift, in January last, from a line; I saw them safe at six o'clock in the evening, and missed them at six in the morning; the prisoner used to go by the house every evening.</p>
