            . I am an officer. I took up the prisoner on the 16th of April, at his house, which is the horse-patrol station, near Cranford; I found these articles in his house; he said they belonged to his wife, and were marked in her maiden name, which was Charlotte Thompson; I know her name is Charlotte.(Property produced and sworn to.)</p>
               <p>The prisoner put in a written defence, stating that he did not know how the linen came to his house, but seeing it there he concluded it to be his wife's.</p>
